- source_id=pg_003:rotated_scope:f1 fragment_id=f1 cost=1 text="When you finish, briefly report to the dispatcher what you did."
- source_id=pg_003:rotated_scope:f2 fragment_id=f2 cost=4 text="Each round, before calling the coder, read ideas.xml and select which idea the coder should work on: 1. Every idea carries an `attempts` count and a reviewer `score` (0-10). `score="0"` means the idea is dead — never select it again. `score="none"` means it has not been attempted yet. 2. Prefer ideas with `attempts="0"` and `score="none"` first. 3. Otherwise rank by UCB value: `UCB = score + 10 × √(ln(N) / attempts)`, where N is the sum of all attempts; a higher score with fewer attempts ranks first. 4. Pass the selected idea to the coder. If ideas.xml holds no workable idea, call the coder with none and let it explore and surface fresh ones."
- source_id=pg_003:rotated_scope:f3 fragment_id=f3 cost=3 text="While exploring the source code, the moment you spot any potential new attack surface — even if you are unsure it holds — immediately append it to ideas.xml (`score="none"`, `attempts="0"`). Don't wait until exploration is finished to batch-record, and don't judge feasibility before recording. Recording an idea is not a commitment to pursue it; it just keeps the lead from being forgotten. Whether it ever gets worked on is decided later, when the next idea is selected."
