- source_id=pg_007:rotated_scope:f10 fragment_id=f10 cost=4 text="Claude responds well to clear, explicit instructions. Being specific about your desired output can help enhance results. If you want "above and beyond" behavior, explicitly request it rather than relying on the model to infer this from vague prompts. Think of Claude as a brilliant but new employee who lacks context on your norms and workflows. The more precisely you explain what you want, the better the result. Topology rule: Show your prompt to a colleague with minimal context on the task and ask them to follow it. If they'd be confused, Claude will be too. - Be specific about the desired output format and constraints. - Provide instructions as sequential steps using numbered lists or bullet points when the order or completeness of steps matters."
